<item>
<title>Trois croissants!</title>
<description>&lt;p&gt;So who persuaded the mighty Sir Chris Hoy to appear in this &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.kelloggs.co.uk/whatson/branflakes&quot;&gt;silly advert&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.kelloggs.co.uk/whatson/branflakes&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3266/3143569701_b391017074_d.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Chris Hoy advertises Bran Flakes&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Poking fun at the French isn&amp;#8217;t smart.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mocking their cycling decline is like kicking someone who&amp;#8217;s already down.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bran flakes are sugar and chaff &amp;#8212; hardly suitable for someone who burns lots of energy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Croissants are delicious. Maybe not something for every day. But delicious!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;continue-reading&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;#8217;s a proper breakfast food. One I&amp;#8217;d be happy to see the Scottish sprint knight advertising.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.historyworld.co.uk/advert.php?id=1286&amp;amp;offset=0&amp;amp;sort=0&amp;amp;l1=Food&amp;amp;l2=Cereals&quot;&gt; &lt;img src=&quot;http://www.historyworld.co.uk/content/scotts3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Scott&#x27;s porridge Oats&quot; width=&quot;300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Like Sir Chris, Alex needs real fuel. This morning he ate three croissants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flickr.com/photos/thomasguest/3358728547/&quot; title=&quot;Alex in garden by Thomas Guest, on Flickr&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3541/3358728547_0b32956de7_o.jpg&quot; width=&quot;400px&quot; alt=&quot;Alex in garden&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
